This article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris and President Joe Biden at the signing of the Respect for Marriage Act into law. The Vice President reflects on past victories for LGBTQ+ rights, such as the legalization of same-sex marriage, and emphasizes the importance of protecting fundamental rights. The President discusses the significance of the law, which recognizes and protects the rights of same-sex couples and interracial couples, and acknowledges the efforts of those who fought for marriage equality. He also highlights the need to continue fighting for equality and justice in the face of challenges, such as the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights. The President signs the bill into law and concludes with a message of love and commitment.